    "Try out: how many vacation days does an employee actually get on a given date? See exactly which layer was applied and why." : "Pr\u00f8v: hvor mange semesterdagar f\u00e5r en medarbetare egentlig p\u00e5 en given dato? Visa pr\u00e6cis hvilket lag som blev p\u00e5f\u00f8rt och hvorfor.",
    "Tue" : "Tir",
    "Tuesday" : "tirsdag",
    "Turn off manual entries if everyone must use the punch clock only." : "Sl\u00e5 manuelle indtastninger fra, hvis alla kun skal bruge punch-uret.",
    "Turn off only if you want to enter every break manually." : "Sluk kun, hvis du vil indtaste hver rast manuelt.",
    "Turn off stamping if your organisation records hours only via manual entries \u2014 the punch clock disappears for all employees." : "Sl\u00e5 stempling fra, hvis din organisation kun registrerer timmar via manuelle indtastninger - punch-uret forsvinsom f\u00f6r alla medarbetare.",
    "Turning this off hides the project picker everywhere and stops you from linking new hours to a project. Projects you already linked stay linked until a manager changes them. Projects with per-person pricing only appear if you are on the project team." : "Hvis du sl\u00e5r dette fra, skjules projektv\u00e6lgeren overalt och forhindrer dig i at linke nye timmar till et projekt. Projekter, du allerede har linket, forbliver knyttet, indtil en chef \u00e6ndrer dem. Projekter med pris pr. person vises kun, hvis du er i projektteamet.",
