    "When employees take breaks, they must write a short reason. This helps ensure breaks are used correctly and comply with labor law." : "N\u00e5r medarbetare teamer raster, skal de skrive en kort begrundelse. Dette er med till at sikre, at raster bruges korrekt och overteamer arbejdslovgivningen.",
    "When enabled, a daily task may copy unused carryover (and optionally unused annual days, see below) into the next calendar year\u2019s opening balance after the carryover deadline, unless a balance already exists for that year. Use the occ command for manual runs." : "N\u00e5r den er aktiveret, kan en daglig opgave kopiere ubrugt overf\u00f8rsel (og eventuelt ubrugte \u00e5rlige dagar, se nedenfor) till det n\u00e6ste kalender\u00e5rs \u00e5bningssaldo efter overf\u00f8rselsfristen, medmindre som allerede eksisterer en saldo f\u00f6r det p\u00e5g\u00e6ldende \u00e5r. Brug kommandoen occ till manuelle k\u00f8rsler.",
    "When enabled, breaks required by German law are automatically added. Disable to manage breaks manually." : "N\u00e5r den er aktiveret, l\u00e4gg tilles raster, som kr\u00e4vs av tysk lov, automatisk. Deaktiver f\u00f6r at hantera raster manuelt.",
    "When enabled, employees can finalize a calendar month to create a tamper-evident snapshot (hash) and PDF. Finalized months stay locked even if this option is turned off later. Reopening a month is limited to administrators." : "N\u00e5r det er aktiveret, kan medarbetarene afslutte en kalenderm\u00e5ned f\u00f6r at oprette et manipulationssikkert snapshot (hash) och PDF. Afsluttede m\u00e5nesom forbliver l\u00e5st, selvom denne mulighed sl\u00e5s fr\u00e5n senere. Gen\u00e5bning en m\u00e5ned er begr\u00e6nset till administratorer.",
    "When enabled, employees cannot seal a month while hours above the bank cap are still unpaid for that month." : "N\u00e5r det er aktiveret, kan medarbetare inte forsegle en m\u00e5ned, mens timmar over bankgr\u00e6nsen stadig er obetalte f\u00f6r den m\u00e5ned.",
    "When enabled, entries that run across midnight (for example 22:00\u201306:00) are shown as two lines in the export (before and after 00:00). This is only a visual/export split \u2013 all internal working time and ArbZG compliance checks continue to use the original, unsplit entry." : "N\u00e5r det er aktiveret, vises poster, som l\u00f8ber over midnat (for eksempel 22:00\u201306:00), som to linjer i eksporten (f\u00f8r och efter 00:00). Dette er kun en visuel/eksportopdeling \u2013 al intern arbejdstid och ArbZG-overensstemmelseskontrol forts\u00e6tter med at bruge den originale, uopdelte post.",
    "When enabled, missing statutory holidays are added when the calendar is viewed. Disable if you want deleted holidays to stay removed." : "N\u00e5r den er aktiveret, l\u00e4gg tilles manglende lagstadgade helgdagar, n\u00e5r kalenderen vises. Deaktiver, hvis du \u00f8nsker, at slettede helgdagar forbliver ta bortet.",
    "When enabled, selected workflow events send email updates to the configured HR recipients." : "N\u00e5r det er aktiveret, sensom udvalgte workflowh\u00e6ndelser e-postopdateringer till de konfigurerede HR-modtagere.",
    "When enabled, transitions to yellow or red levels can trigger in-app and email notifications." : "N\u00e5r det er aktiveret, kan overgange till gule eller r\u00f8de niveauer udl\u00f8se aviseringar i appen och e-post.",
    "When on: managers are taken from the ArbeitszeitCheck teams you define below. When off: managers are determined from shared Nextcloud groups (default behaviour)." : "N\u00e5r t\u00e6ndt: chefer tages fr\u00e5n de ArbeitszeitCheck-team, du definerer nedenfor. N\u00e5r deaktiveret: chefer bestemmes ud fr\u00e5n delte Nextcloud-grupper (standardadf\u00e6rd).",
    "When someone works too many hours or doesn't take required breaks, the system will send a notification to managers and the employee." : "N\u00e5r nogen arbejsom f\u00f6r mange timmar eller inte teamer de n\u00f8dvendige raster, sensom systemet en meddelelse till chefer och medarbetaren.",
    "When this rule applies" : "N\u00e5r denne regel g\u00e6lder",
    "When you finished. Night shifts: use the next calendar day if end is after midnight." : "N\u00e5r du er f\u00e6rdig. Nattevagter: Brug den n\u00e6ste kalenderdag, hvis slutningen er efter midnat.",
    "When you started (e.g. 09:00)." : "Da du startede (t.ex. 09:00).",
    "Which German State?" : "Hvilken tysk stat?",
